lScope></bibl></example><example><quote>zæǧʒynæ jyn? bæg˳ydær уn zæǧʒynæn</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>скажешь ты ему? конечно скажу</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>will you tell him? of course, I will</q></tr></example></exampleGrp><etym xml:lang="ru">Из %ibæ%i + %ik˳y%i? — см. частицу <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ba"/> и <ref type="xr" target="#entry_k0y"/> ‘когда’. Или кавказский вклад?—ср. <mentioned xml:lang="ce"><lang/> <w>baqh-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="bbl"><lang/> <w>bage</w> <gloss><q>верный</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="bbl"><w/> <gloss><q>правильный</q></gloss></mentioned>, .%n<bibl><author>Schiefner</author><biblScope xml:lang="ru">Versuch uber die Tusch-Sprache, стр. 143</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">Versuch uber die Tusch-Sprache, p. 143</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">From %ibæ%i + %ik˳y%i? — see the particle <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ba"/> and <ref type="xr" target="#entry_k0y"/> ‘when’. Or is it a Caucasian contribution? — cf. <mentioned xml:lang="ce"><lang/> <w>baqh-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="bbl"><lang/> <w>bage</w> <gloss><q>devoted</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="bbl"><w/> <gloss><q>right</q></gloss></mentioned>, .%n<bibl><author>Schiefner</author><biblScope xml:lang="ru">Versuch uber die Tusch-Sprache, стр. 143</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">Versuch uber die Tusch-Sprache, p. 143</biblScope></bibl>.</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>